					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Would it be possible to pretend to have a 24-bit address space, where the upper 4 bits select which chip we're looking at?
<br /><ul><li>$000000-$00FFFF: CPU address space </li><li>$600000-$602FFF: PPU address space </li><li>$603F00-$603F1F: Palette </li><li>$700000-$7000FF: OAM </li><li>$800000-$BFFFFF: All PRG ROM banks </li><li>$C00000-$DFFFFF: All CHR ROM or CHR RAM banks </li><li>$E00000-$FFFFFF: All PRG RAM banks </li></ul></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
